<br>
There is a button called &quot;advanced.&quot;  Either click on that or hit your V key.  That will bring up the AA skill menu.  In the upper right corner there are buttons to set what percentage of exp goes to AA points rather than regular exp.<br>
<br>
Most, myself included, recommending getting run 3 quickly.  After that, opinions vary, but I think the majority view leveling as more important than AA points.  Leveling gives you more powerful spells, better chances to resist mob spells, and lesser chances they will resist your spells.  The better AA skills also require you to be higher level than you are now.  One case in which you might be better off doing AA points than leveling is if you are killing Nagafen or Vox regularly and don't want to stop that anytime soon.  Then it would make sense to stockpile points till you are done killing them, then hit 55 and spend some of those points.  For when you do hit 55, casting mastery and casting fury are the routes most mages take to spend twelve points in arch in order to unlock the class skills.  By unlocking I mean you have to spend so many points in order to have access to another tab on the AA page.  You have to spend six points on general skills before you can spend any points on arch skills.  You then have to spend twelve additional points in arch in order to have access to the class skills.  PoP skills are a bit different and don't require that you have spent X amount of points in class, but many of them do have other prerequisites that you must fullfil before you can buy those skills.  Eventually they go back and spend points on durability, mental clarity, and subtilty.  For class skills, pet hold is very nice and some mages really like the others.  I'm indifferent to most of them, but some are quite powerful given certain play styles.  As far as PoP skills go, I forget the level requirements for most of the skills, but there are some useful ones when you get to that level.<br>
<br>
I haven't found any uses for research other than to make pets for mages lower level than myself.<br>
<br>
Spell drops depend on the expansion.  By that I mean Kunark spells drop on Kunark, Velious spells drop on Velious, and so on.  The 51-54 Kunark spells you can solo for, though they sell for so little now it would probably be much easier to hit the Bazaar and spending 50pp each to get all of them.  The 55+ spells tend to sell for a bit more since they aren't quite as common, but their prices are still reasonable for the most part.  Muzzle of Mardu and Burnout 4 are probably the most expensive non PoP spells since the former only drops off Juggernauts in Sebilis and the later off dragons in Western Wastes.  If I had to guess, the average price for 55-60th level spells would be around 500pp with some being higher and some lower.  Some spells only drop in certain locations off specific mobs.  I've already mentioned two.  Velocity off Juggs and Shard of the Core off Holgarish (dangerous caster flying monkeys if not careful) are two more examples.<br>
<br>
I hope this helps.  Non PoP spells for the most part aren't expensive anymore and it is frequently easier to head to the Bazaar and buy them than it is to spend days or weeks camping them and hoping for a lucky drop.<br>
